				\begin{document}$$P \% =\frac{{W}_{w}-{W}_{d}}{\rho b\,\ast \,{V}_{m}}\times 100 \% $$\end{document}P%=Ww−Wdρb∗Vm×100%where Wd is the dry weight of membrane, Ww is the wet weight of membrane, ρb is the density of n-butanol and Vm is the volume of the membrane.

